	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002052_0001"><!--pb/@n='73r'--></pb>

<lb/><p><placeName><settlement type="town">Hamilton</settlement></placeName><date when="1864-08-30"><del>30</del></date><date when="1864-08-29"><add place="inline">29</add><choice><abbr>Aug.</abbr><expan>August</expan></choice>
<lb/>1864</date></p>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I did not
<lb/><choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> yours of <date when="1864-08-20">20<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date>
<lb/>till my return from
<lb/><placeName><region>The Highlands</region></placeName> the day
<lb/>before yesterday -</p>
<lb/><p>I return to <placeName><settlement type="city">London</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>in the course of a
<lb/>few days and will
<lb/>be very happy to
<lb/>go with the <persName>Adrmiral</persName>
<lb/>at any time he
<lb/>chooses to the Admirally
<lb/>on your account</p>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002052_0002"><!--pb/@n='73v'--></pb>
<lb/><p>The Paymaster of the
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Seringapatam</settlement></placeName> having
<lb/>neglected to send home
<lb/>the papers containing
<lb/>the deductions for
<lb/>slops &amp;c prevented
<lb/>the other men getting
<lb/>their pay as soon
<lb/>as they otherwise
<lb/>might have done -
<lb/>I gave certificates
<lb/>from memory
<lb/>for all hands - Your
<w><lb break="no"/>-self</w> included before
<lb/>my departure fro<supplied cert="high">m</supplied></p>
			
</div>
